7665,-0.01649369,-0.05547171,-0.00077631,0.02424893,0.01246099,-0.00885813,0.04123954,0.00006615,0.04022427,-0.02937705,0.00577981,0.06755476,0.03730711,-0.06493443,0.0325795,-0.00506257,-0.00286373,-0.01904769,0.02323478,-0.02966532,-0.00702544,-0.01002743,0.00061971,-0.04058204,-0.02666738,0.04206927,0.01556127,-0.03416509,-0.01661121,0.01265137,0.04010481,0.00608152,0.04284509,0.00395753,0.00304542,-0.01343534,-0.00718634,0.0345943,-0.0204384,-0.00059814,-0.00273285,-0.00131879,-0.00901216,-0.01606882,0.01654712,0.01518046,0.09450578,0.04146381,-0.02323599,-0.06752504,-0.00765203,-0.00723208,0.02266901,-0.04251191,-0.03965565,-0.04383186,-0.04092473,0.00501903,-0.00564592,0.00162577,0.0219151,0.0337201,0.00481712,0.01393964,0.00253235,-0.02174709,0.00351258,-0.01879436,0.01952429,0.02508871,0.03219866,0.02081573,-0.00820285,-0.06007551,-0.00138268,0.03594481,-0.02510867,-0.03413694,0.02490072,-0.04301392,-0.02502346,0.00834759,-0.07741724,-0.08256476,0.00040782,0.03898066,0.09368098,-0.01837227,-0.00983933,-0.02468795,0.04535247,-0.02734929,0.05874998,-0.0235771,0.00143188,0.01822116,0.06189402,-0.03569308,0.01232394,0.02999084,0.00660992,0.08042995,0.00176327,-0.03077249,-0.0673549,0.05569812,0.0504176,-0.00279033,-0.05174505,-0.03443666,0.00000121,0.04524783,0.02549306,-0.05961214,0.00505725,0.01339456,0.0176528,0.01452204,-0.07825201,0.04182453],"last_embed":{"hash":"6b9ee57f04ea908a2860d6cf6e779ce5bd1c5a1bc6be1a923c807cf81b96e356","tokens":2708}}},"text":null,"length":0,"last_read":{"hash":"6b9ee57f04ea908a2860d6cf6e779ce5bd1c5a1bc6be1a923c807cf81b96e356","at":1742533454025},"key":"DDD 的实战（第十章）.md#Conceptual Contours#{1}","lines":[87,132],"size":7609,"outlinks":[{"title":"Sometimes people chop functionality fine to allow flexible combination. Sometimes they lump it large to encapsulate complexity.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":1},{"title":"When elements of a model or design are embedded in a monolithic construct, their functionality gets duplicated. The external interface doesn’t say everything a client might care about. Their meaning is hard to understand, because different concepts are mixed together.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":4},{"title":"On the other hand, breaking down classes and methods can pointlessly complicate the  client, forcing client objects to understand how tiny pieces fit together.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":6},{"title":"Half of a uranium atom is not uranium. And of course,it isn’t just grain size that counts, but just where the grain runs.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":8},{"title":"But there is rhyme and reason somewhere, or else modeling would be pointless.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":10},{"title":"To avoid slipping into a mechanistic view of them, temper your technical thinking by frequently touching base with your intuition for the domain.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":12},{"title":"slipping into","target":"slipping into","line":14},{"title":"Is this an expedient based on a particular set of relationships in the current model and code, or doesit echo some contour of the underlying domain?","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":16},{"title":"Clumping things that don’t need to be dissected or rearranged avoids clutter and makes it easier to see the elements that really are meant to recombine.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":18},{"title":"Decompose design elements (operations, interfaces, classes, and AGGREGATES) into cohesive units, taking into consideration your intuition of the important divisions in the domain.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":20},{"title":"it’s hard to produce up front. But it may never emerge from technically oriented refactoring; it emerges from refactoring toward deeper insight.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":23},{"title":"When successive refactoring tends to be localized, not shaking multiple broad concepts of the model, it is an indicator of model fit.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":26},{"title":"The new model contained only one more object than the old one, yet the partitioning of responsibility had been greatly changed.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":30},{"title":"Schedules, which had been worked out through case logic in the Calculator classes, were exploded into discrete classes for different types of fees and interest. On the other hand, payments of fees and interest,previously kept separate, were lumped together.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":34},{"title":"But had she found aCONCEPTUAL CONTOUR that will help the domain design change and grow as the application and the business evolve? There can be no guarantees about how a design will handle unanticipated change, but shethought it had improved the odds.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":38},{"title":"As the project proceeded, a requirement emerged for detailed rules for handling early and late payments.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":41},{"title":"Nor did it come because she made a design so versatile it could accommodate any conceivable change. It happened because in the previous refactoring, the design was aligned with underlying concepts of the domain.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":43},{"title":"INTENTION-REVEALING INTERFACES allow clients to present objects as units of meaning rather than just mechanisms. SIDE-EFFECT-FREE FUNCTIONS and ASSERTIONS make it safe to use those units and make complex combinations. The emergence of CONCEPTUAL CONTOURS stabilizes parts of the model and also makes the units more intuitive to use and combine.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":45}],"class_name":"SmartBlock"},
