4556367,-0.01864422,-0.06254184,-0.01207503,-0.06181356,0.01256316,-0.00069915,0.03234785,-0.02445828,0.02689318,0.03603942,0.03523476,-0.03727213,0.00973509,0.09744048,0.00816399,-0.02724746,0.05908202,-0.01444235,-0.01665334,-0.01004818,0.04741326,-0.06473032,-0.04171852,0.00125036,-0.02059904,0.03127952,-0.0144045,0.05664154,0.00899021,-0.01140465,-0.02878349,0.02312727,0.10270631,0.01559927,0.00300469,0.00988671,-0.00431973,-0.0608807,-0.00345346,0.02344647,-0.01054612,0.00432421,-0.00545918,-0.01228767,-0.08075005,-0.02188776,0.00321901,0.02363219,0.0760226,0.02144729,0.00007506,-0.08003227,-0.00819018,-0.00661186,0.01330424,-0.01464873,-0.04163273,-0.04550958,-0.03518167,-0.00412447,-0.00738951,0.00709051,0.05383,0.06367792,-0.04537529,0.01199659,0.02053039,-0.07669535,0.00757832,-0.02091955,0.0293892,0.04663157,0.00922281,0.02351058,-0.00127946,-0.01517311,0.0207139,0.05598599,-0.00460461,-0.04823349,0.00693448,-0.01660599,-0.00200608,-0.01364291,-0.03649043,-0.06117685,-0.0140073,0.05788087,0.01477004,-0.01686632,0.00585569,-0.00874249,0.04069081,-0.00593986,0.07499938,-0.02329697,-0.0319369,0.03950252,0.03573116,-0.06595375,0.00320536,-0.0131914,0.01979147,0.06866822,-0.03051442,0.00288795,-0.06382787,0.03730392,-0.01883187,0.02498708,-0.04127107,0.00130034,0.00000123,0.03820789,0.03112132,-0.0296974,-0.01994731,0.01421274,0.00427561,-0.0075213,-0.05229976,0.01412615],"last_embed":{"hash":"1495744e4d571e431b60a034ba35b0c109550e047c0a8adda4de56bd42394157","tokens":1212}}},"text":null,"length":0,"last_read":{"hash":"1495744e4d571e431b60a034ba35b0c109550e047c0a8adda4de56bd42394157","at":1742533456146},"key":"DDD 的实战（第十章）.md#Extending SPECFICATION in a Declarative Style","lines":[195,213],"size":3454,"outlinks":[{"title":"SPECIFICATION is an adaptation of an established formalism, the predicate. Predicates have other useful properties that we can draw on, selectively.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":3},{"title":"However, other implementation options are possible that would minimize object count or boost speed, or perhaps be compatible with idiosyncratic technologies present in some project.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":5},{"title":"When you want to test a candidate, you have to interpret this structure, which can be done by popping off each element, then evaluating it or popping off the next as required by an operator. You would end up with this:","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":7},{"title":"You have to find an implementation with trade-offs that work for your circumstances. The same pattern and model can underlie very different implementations.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":9},{"title":"But what they asked for was a list of chemicals whose handling has become more stringent. Perhaps there are none in-house right now, or perhaps they just happened to be packed into a more stringent container. In either case, the report just described would not list them.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":11},{"title":"In most situations it is best to avoid such complexity by making a choice, either forgoing some of the operators or forgoing subsumption.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":13},{"title":"This might be a point where the granularity is too coarse. The conventional approach would be to break the calculation methods down into subroutines.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":15},{"title":"Model concepts are decoupled; operations entangle a minimum of other types.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":17}],"class_name":"SmartBlock"},
