564,-0.05683327,-0.0016691,0.00716094,-0.00707395,0.08806981,-0.01419762,-0.01356312,-0.08137608,-0.01578767,-0.00279916,0.01490071,0.00388504,-0.04977512,-0.049874,-0.00281811,-0.02506869,-0.00434202,-0.00332316,0.0536356,0.04504777,-0.0488337,0.00196393,0.01049487,-0.02783883,0.01559355,0.00823301,0.01797884,0.02674909,0.03055715,-0.0105904,-0.02924293,-0.00092282,0.04634126,0.04520331,-0.05261854,-0.03945773,0.02499563,0.00625978,-0.03580828,-0.00617905,-0.06083359,-0.07459727,0.01459146,0.03770824,0.05531665,-0.00712726,0.00806738,-0.01861978,0.04234295,-0.03019468,0.05803831,-0.00416147,-0.01010143,0.02428335,0.02996858,-0.08356313,0.0068396,0.00580222,-0.00873776,0.04475113,0.00313451,-0.02973596,-0.07537307,0.03859844,0.01100078,0.00063604,-0.03196608,-0.01879996,0.00000123,0.01223968,-0.00167042,-0.04543055,-0.01472239,0.0342576,0.00083714,-0.01411776,-0.07519703,0.02635087],"last_embed":{"hash":"bbcbecb8c7dff5dc51c82d40f421dacb5556bd97e82a7bb99dc02903781b85dd","tokens":1461}}},"text":null,"length":0,"last_read":{"hash":"bbcbecb8c7dff5dc51c82d40f421dacb5556bd97e82a7bb99dc02903781b85dd","at":1742533808681},"key":"DDD 的实战（第十章）.md#Assertions","lines":[59,84],"size":3951,"outlinks":[{"title":"Separating complex computations into SIDE-EFFECT-FREE FUNCTIONS cuts the problem down to size, butthere is still a residue of commands on the ENTITIES that produce side effects, and anyone using them mustunderstand their consequences.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":3},{"title":"We need a way of understanding the meaning of a design element and the consequences of executing anoperation without delving into its internals.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":5},{"title":"“design by contract”","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":7},{"title":"Seek models with coherent sets of concepts, which lead a developer to infer theintended ASSERTIONS, accelerating the learning curve and reducing the risk ofcontradictory code.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":10},{"title":"Because ASSERTIONS are all in terms of states, rather than procedures, they make tests easyto write.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":12},{"title":"Theoretically, any noncontradictory set of assertions would work. But humans don’t just compile predicates in their heads.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":15},{"title":"While developers were pondering this option, they made a discovery.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":17},{"title":"So, to make the volume model logically consistent would make it unsuitable for its application requirements.There seems to be a dilemma.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":19},{"title":"As we search for a better model, we have significant advantages over the original designers, because of the knowledge crunching and refactoring to deeper insight that has happened in the interim.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":21},{"title":"The next ingredient in recombinable elements is effective decomposition. . . .","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":24}],"class_name":"SmartBlock"},
