6,-0.00748763,-0.06077446,0.00113454,0.00835006,-0.00082709,0.0860849,-0.01253646,-0.01713354,-0.07969567,-0.01586425,0.00167556,0.01469939,-0.0037321,-0.04531239,-0.0551631,-0.00611845,-0.02880529,-0.00458474,-0.00223672,0.04420059,0.04506249,-0.04628201,0.00190313,0.00898118,-0.0275571,0.01717664,0.00606812,0.01757878,0.02896426,0.0176731,-0.0028336,-0.02721004,-0.00139845,0.04895877,0.04482424,-0.05433419,-0.04574979,0.01457995,0.00504381,-0.03377741,-0.00838874,-0.06494985,-0.07853346,0.016807,0.04060609,0.06478678,-0.00279638,0.00192064,-0.01937322,0.04358556,-0.03142849,0.06009124,-0.00179525,-0.00031727,0.0190328,0.02797594,-0.08207788,0.01406339,0.00436077,-0.0153488,0.04064167,0.01145248,-0.02685103,-0.07001317,0.03223414,0.01570276,0.0049026,-0.02927396,-0.01755825,0.00000124,0.00716313,0.00654905,-0.04844556,-0.01277297,0.03310419,0.00862975,-0.01151442,-0.08254675,0.02954175],"last_embed":{"hash":"e799eb24717d52ba0f4dc43b874b726eb133abaa3a5c3372aa58c5668757b575","tokens":1461}}},"text":null,"length":0,"last_read":{"hash":"e799eb24717d52ba0f4dc43b874b726eb133abaa3a5c3372aa58c5668757b575","at":1742533809028},"key":"DDD 的实战（第十章）.md#Assertions#{1}","lines":[61,84],"size":3937,"outlinks":[{"title":"Separating complex computations into SIDE-EFFECT-FREE FUNCTIONS cuts the problem down to size, butthere is still a residue of commands on the ENTITIES that produce side effects, and anyone using them mustunderstand their consequences.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":1},{"title":"We need a way of understanding the meaning of a design element and the consequences of executing anoperation without delving into its internals.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":3},{"title":"“design by contract”","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":5},{"title":"Seek models with coherent sets of concepts, which lead a developer to infer theintended ASSERTIONS, accelerating the learning curve and reducing the risk ofcontradictory code.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":8},{"title":"Because ASSERTIONS are all in terms of states, rather than procedures, they make tests easyto write.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":10},{"title":"Theoretically, any noncontradictory set of assertions would work. But humans don’t just compile predicates in their heads.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":13},{"title":"While developers were pondering this option, they made a discovery.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":15},{"title":"So, to make the volume model logically consistent would make it unsuitable for its application requirements.There seems to be a dilemma.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":17},{"title":"As we search for a better model, we have significant advantages over the original designers, because of the knowledge crunching and refactoring to deeper insight that has happened in the interim.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":19},{"title":"The next ingredient in recombinable elements is effective decomposition. . . .","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":22}],"class_name":"SmartBlock"},
