2698719,-0.09017621,-0.02485719,-0.00939437,0.00862621,0.07655812,-0.02981658,0.00697236,-0.04885552,0.00051546,-0.01161363,0.03072979,0.00726199,-0.03356258,-0.05127187,-0.00153548,-0.02571216,-0.00903609,0.00967763,0.04323838,0.06122296,-0.04612917,-0.00093904,0.02961856,-0.04019247,0.002764,-0.00435496,0.03166385,0.01587535,0.02565818,0.01847402,-0.02629542,-0.0028562,0.00252088,0.01730854,-0.03157508,-0.04102378,0.01516774,-0.01901996,-0.00399968,-0.00627147,-0.05825945,-0.07628125,-0.01216101,0.08224077,0.03773727,-0.01461811,-0.00941446,-0.03455823,0.0570632,-0.01802667,0.07602353,0.00382839,-0.00636206,0.03581542,0.06690823,-0.08901206,0.04808965,-0.00159139,-0.03171785,0.02975918,0.02565304,-0.01281613,-0.06280366,0.02919273,-0.00660054,-0.00295383,-0.05431999,-0.01933992,0.00000131,0.00197929,-0.00287882,-0.08338279,-0.01709457,-0.00662055,0.01532341,-0.01131104,-0.05079675,0.01589279],"last_embed":{"hash":"486fff3ba2a94fb90be1e9b43e9e84ec501f6f3694868eab71da23e7c21b4401","tokens":950}}},"text":null,"length":0,"last_read":{"hash":"486fff3ba2a94fb90be1e9b43e9e84ec501f6f3694868eab71da23e7c21b4401","at":1742533810828},"key":"DDD 的实战（第十章）.md#Declarative Design#{1}","lines":[173,186],"size":2683,"outlinks":[{"title":"ASSERTIONS can lead to much better designs, even with our relatively informal way of testing them.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":1},{"title":"This is tedious and fraught with error, and the bulk of it obscures the meaning of our model. (Some languages are better than others, but all require us to do a lot of grunt work.)","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":3},{"title":"Generating a running program from a declaration of model properties is a kind of Holy Grail of MODEL-DRIVEN DESIGN, but it does have its pitfalls in practice.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":5},{"title":"The unintended consequence of many attempts at declarative design is the dumbing-down of the model and application, as developers, trapped by the limitations of the framework, enact design triage in order to get something delivered.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":7},{"title":"This control code introduces side effects, so that the behavior is no longer dictated completely by the declared rules. Adding, removing, or reordering the rules can cause unexpected,incorrect results. Therefore, a logic programmer has to be careful to keep the effect of code obvious, just as anobject programmer does.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":11},{"title":"The best ofthese unburden developers of drudge work while leaving them complete freedom to design.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":13}],"class_name":"SmartBlock"},
